Program: Crossing Continents
Title: Central African Republic: A Road Through Hatred
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b04009c0
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 14 Apr 2014
How do you restore peace to a country now being torn apart by a vicious campaign of ethnic and religious cleansing? Two men in the Central African Republic believe they have the answer - friendship. Tim Whewell joins the Catholic Archbishop of Bangui, Dieudonne Nzapalainga and the country's Chief Imam, Oumar Kobine Layama as they travel across the country trying to reconcile Christian and Muslim communities. Show less